Linux Sound

ALSA is the Kernel space interface to sound on Linux.
ALSA provides a user-land API called `libasound' with documentation here: http://www.alsa-project.org/alsa-doc/alsa-lib/

My goal with this practice program is to generate a simple signal and have it play back through the speakers.

Requirements:

- Linux Headers # apt-get install linux-headers-generic
- Alsa sounds # gcc -lasound, #include <alsa/asoundlib.h>
- C Math lib # gcc -lm, #include <math.h>
- GCC

Setup:

> cd /path/to/project
> source env/shell

Build:

> build

Run:

> run

Debug:

> debug